'''Lowickan Firegems''' were a highly illegal form of [[Firegem]]s. They were mined in the [[Lowick asteroid belt|Lowick]] [[Asteroid field/Legends|asteroid belt]] in the [[Pa'Lowick system|Pa'Lowick]] [[Star system/Legends|system]].<ref name="TBS">''[[The Truce at Bakura Sourcebook]]''</ref> They were deep [[Color/Legends|red]] in color and glowed due to the internal molecular vibration of the gem. They were typically between four and six [[Centimeter/Legends|centimeters]] in size, with smooth rounded edges.<ref name="Gundark">''[[Gundark's Fantastic Technology: Personal Gear]]''</ref>

During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]] conducted experiments with Firegems to use them as high-energy power sources. The Pa'lowick system was quarantined and a task force of [[Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyers]] and [[Imperial Office of Customs/Legends|Imperial Customs]] cruisers patrolled the region to keep out trespassers. They also would detonate to high levels of radiation found in [[Starship/Legends|starship]] reactor cores, making them highly dangerous.<ref name="TBS" /> This led them to be used to sabotage the [[Engine/Legends|engines]] of starships. The firegem would be smuggled on-board in a radiation-proof [[Magnetic field/Legends|magnetic field]] and inserted in the [[reactor injector module]]. When the ship made the jump to [[Hyperspace/Legends|hyperspace]], the field would break down and expose the firegem to intense radiation. The exposure would create a harmonic resonance inside the firegem and cause an explosion. According to entries in [[Gundark's Gear Datalog]] by [[Yideg]] and [[Kollan]], the firegems were easier to find after the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] but the [[New Republic Intelligence Service|NRI]] and [[Sector Ranger/Legends|Sector Rangers]] had raised the threat level of the firegems and were working on new scanning technologies to detect them.<ref name="Gundark" />

